                <p>&ensp;What you will see at the link below is the final project I did during my One Month HTML class in Sept 2016. I started with no HTML experience and in 30 days had enough knowledge of HTML and CSS (another  language used alongside HTML) to produce several sites. With each project, we learned of various web resources the developers use daily. These free resources such as Bootstrap.com and stackoverflow.com make finding pre-written code and getting your questions answered easy. There are many in the developer comunity that share their knowledge freely and openly. <br>
                
                &ensp; HTML can be used alongside CSS and Javascript to give the content of your page some style and special effects. HTML provides the words and images shown on a site, CSS gives those elements some style, such as font and font size in the case of text or scale as in the case for images.  CSS also allows one to make a page layout changes as the browser window or device form factor changes..so a site looks good on a lap-top and a phone. <br>

